===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{cattag|Leninism}} The intermediate phase of social development between [[capitalism]] and full [[communism]]. This is a strategy whereby the government has control of all key resource-producing industries and manages most aspects of the market, in stark opposition to [[capitalism]].
# A political philosophy that supports social and economic equality, collective decision-making{{,}} and public control of productive capital and natural resources to some degree, as advocated by [[socialist]]s.
# The socialist political philosophies as a group, including [[Marxism]], [[libertarian socialism]], [[democratic socialism]], and [[social democracy]].

